1
00:00:05,948 --> 00:00:08,402
Jagannāth is Kṛṣṇa in Dvārakā

2
00:00:08,402 --> 00:00:14,868
feeling incomparable separation
from Vṛndāvan,

3
00:00:14,868 --> 00:00:17,801
from Rādhārāṇī
and the Vraja-gopīs in Vṛndāvan.

4
00:00:17,801 --> 00:00:22,875
That’s who Jagannāth is. 
That’s why He looks like that.

5
00:00:23,175 --> 00:00:27,260
[The Gift of Appreciation]

6
00:00:27,598 --> 00:00:31,517
This is an ecstatic transformation 
of feeling separation

7
00:00:31,517 --> 00:00:37,610
from Rādhārāṇī and the Vraja-gopīs, 
and He’s stunned.

8
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:45,201
So, if in that position, 
you can take, begin

9
00:00:45,201 --> 00:00:52,444
—talking about beginnings—
if you can begin to take Him to Vṛndāvan,

10
00:00:52,444 --> 00:00:59,777
what better beginning 
could you ever conceive of beginnings?

11
00:00:59,777 --> 00:01:04,873
What beginning
would be superior to this one?

12
00:01:04,873 --> 00:01:11,350
It’s the ultimate beginning.
The best, ever.

13
00:01:11,350 --> 00:01:14,816
I remember hearing
Prabhupād say,

14
00:01:14,816 --> 00:01:20,491
“It’s the emotional ecstasy
of taking Kṛṣṇa to Vṛndāvan.”

15
00:01:20,577 --> 00:01:23,934
Because when I joined, ’71,

16
00:01:23,934 --> 00:01:32,454
around the—by Gurudev’s grace—
Nṛsiṁha Chaturdaśī, a few days before,

17
00:01:32,454 --> 00:01:37,852
the Daśamī,
which was the day after my birthday,

18
00:01:37,852 --> 00:01:39,946
so it all worked out …

19
00:01:39,946 --> 00:01:44,555
So within two months, 
Prabhupād showed up

20
00:01:44,555 --> 00:01:48,815
in San Francisco
for the Ratha Yātrā.

21
00:01:51,697 --> 00:01:54,791
And I once said to 
Guru Mahārāj about it,

22
00:01:54,791 --> 00:01:57,433
I said … you know, I was 19,

23
00:01:57,433 --> 00:01:59,562
and so many others
were very young,

24
00:01:59,562 --> 00:02:01,669
and suddenly we were like, 
immersed,

25
00:02:01,669 --> 00:02:07,148
—you talk about immersion, 
total immersion—

26
00:02:07,148 --> 00:02:11,004
we were totally immersed
in all of these things

27
00:02:11,004 --> 00:02:16,683
and on some level, I was saying,
on some level appreciating it.

28
00:02:16,683 --> 00:02:20,343
And Guru Mahārāj said,
“Yes, He extended you

29
00:02:20,343 --> 00:02:23,973
the capacity to appreciate it.”

30
00:02:23,973 --> 00:02:26,636
That’s what it is.

31
00:02:26,636 --> 00:02:29,480
That’s what the whole
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness is,

32
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:35,349
the extended appreciation, 
capacity, to appreciate it;

33
00:02:35,349 --> 00:02:38,147
what Mahāprabhu did
to Sārvabhauma;

34
00:02:38,147 --> 00:02:41,948
what everyone, every extension,
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness

35
00:02:41,948 --> 00:02:45,900
has ever been;
a gracious merciful extension,

36
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:49,021
extended capacity, 
to appreciate that.

37
00:02:49,021 --> 00:02:51,280
Reality for Itself, by Itself.

38
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,404
Guru-rūpa-harim gauram:

39
00:02:53,404 --> 00:02:58,468
Mahāprabhu comes 
in Rādhārāṇī’s [mood]

40
00:02:58,468 --> 00:03:00,045
to preach Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

41
00:03:00,045 --> 00:03:03,184
Why didn’t he preach
some other way?

42
00:03:03,553 --> 00:03:06,660
Because there’s nothing superior to that, 
He couldn’t th[ink] …

43
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:10,193
This is, in His estimation, 
the most superior.

44
00:03:10,193 --> 00:03:13,616
When He saw what She has,
that awakened in Him

45
00:03:13,616 --> 00:03:17,398
the tendency 
to distribute this also.

46
00:03:17,398 --> 00:03:20,391
The highest thing. 
The best.

47
00:03:20,391 --> 00:03:25,590
And it reaches its zenith 
at this pastime.

48
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:29,287
And that’s why
Guru Mahārāj says,

49
00:03:29,287 --> 00:03:32,669
Saraswatī Ṭhākur:
“Vṛndāvan’s for the shallow thinkers.”

50
00:03:32,669 --> 00:03:34,775
He got that from
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur,

51
00:03:34,775 --> 00:03:37,842
“Kurukṣetra’s for the man 
of real bhajan.”

52
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:40,506
Now we’re back to this,
saying,

53
00:03:40,506 --> 00:03:44,390
because separation
has reached it’s zenith,

54
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:47,296
whoever will render service 
at that time

55
00:03:47,296 --> 00:03:51,714
will draw
the maximum remuneration.

56
00:03:51,714 --> 00:03:53,611
That’s why
it’s the best time,

57
00:03:53,611 --> 00:03:56,933
and that’s why on this day,
at this time,

58
00:03:56,933 --> 00:04:00,502
with this concept
and this understanding,

59
00:04:00,502 --> 00:04:06,657
Guru Mahārāj began 
Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh.

60
00:04:06,657 --> 00:04:10,130
It’s the beginning
of the Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh.

61
00:04:10,130 --> 00:04:11,957
This moment, this point.

62
00:04:11,957 --> 00:04:14,000
Nothing Guru Mahārāj does
is by accident,

63
00:04:14,965 --> 00:04:18,087
and everything is multi-layered, 
multi-dimensional,

64
00:04:18,087 --> 00:04:22,118
and profound 
to the infinite degree.

65
00:04:22,118 --> 00:04:25,024
He’s bringing you
in connection with the pinnacle

66
00:04:25,024 --> 00:04:26,905
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

67
00:04:26,905 --> 00:04:31,414
that’s when he starts; 
his Maṭh springs out of that plane,

68
00:04:31,414 --> 00:04:35,835
and his Maṭh proper takes people
into that plane.

69
00:04:35,835 --> 00:04:37,886
That’s what he’s doing,

70
00:04:37,886 --> 00:04:41,444
and that’s why
nothing compares to it.

